  "prompt": "How does international law intersect with national laws on money laundering?",
  "response": "International law intersects with national laws on money laundering through several key mechanisms:\n\n1. International Conventions and Treaties\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Establish common standards and principles for combating money laundering\n\n2. Mutual Legal Assistance\n- Countries collaborate on investigations\n- Share financial intelligence\n- Extradite suspects\n- Enforce cross-border legal actions\n\n3. Regulatory Harmonization\n- Develop consistent legal frameworks\n- Standardize reporting requirements\n- Create similar compliance mechanisms\n- Reduce regulatory arbitrage\n\n4. Global Compliance Standards\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Customer due diligence requirements\n- Anti-money laundering (AML) protocols\n\n5. International Financial Institutions\n- World Bank\n- International Monetary Fund\n- Provide guidance and support\n- Monitor national implementation\n- Offer technical assistance\n\n6. Information Sharing Networks\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n- Cross-border communication platforms\n- Real-time intelligence exchange\n- Coordinated enforcement efforts\n\nThese interactions create a complex, multilayered approach to preventing and prosecuting money laundering globally.",
